From: Bo-Cun Chen <bc-bocun.chen@mediatek.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Sep 2025 12:56:55 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: mtk_ppe: align PPE aging time with flow
 offload GC interval

The PPE ages out entries earlier than the flow offload garbage collection
work when traffic stops for a duration longer than the PPE TCP/UDP aging
out time. During this period, the flow offload GC does not teardown the
flow rule. As a result, the flow offload cannot immediately reallocate a
new flow rule when traffic resumes.

Change TCP aging from 7 to 30 seconds and UDP aging from 12 to 30
seconds to align with the flow offload GC interval and prevent premature
entry expiration.

Signed-off-by: Bo-Cun Chen <bc-bocun.chen@mediatek.com>
[dpawlik: ported from mtk-openwrt-feeds 25.12 999-ppe-12]
Signed-off-by: Daniel Pawlik <dpawlik@redhat.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_ppe.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_ppe.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_ppe.c
@@ -1086,12 +1086,12 @@ void mtk_ppe_start(struct mtk_ppe *ppe)
 	      FIELD_PREP(MTK_PPE_UNBIND_AGE_DELTA, 3);
 	ppe_w32(ppe, MTK_PPE_UNBIND_AGE, val);
 
-	val = FIELD_PREP(MTK_PPE_BIND_AGE0_DELTA_UDP, 12) |
+	val = FIELD_PREP(MTK_PPE_BIND_AGE0_DELTA_UDP, 30) |
 	      FIELD_PREP(MTK_PPE_BIND_AGE0_DELTA_NON_L4, 1);
 	ppe_w32(ppe, MTK_PPE_BIND_AGE0, val);
 
 	val = FIELD_PREP(MTK_PPE_BIND_AGE1_DELTA_TCP_FIN, 1) |
-	      FIELD_PREP(MTK_PPE_BIND_AGE1_DELTA_TCP, 7);
+	      FIELD_PREP(MTK_PPE_BIND_AGE1_DELTA_TCP, 30);
 	ppe_w32(ppe, MTK_PPE_BIND_AGE1, val);
 
 	val = MTK_PPE_BIND_LIMIT0_QUARTER | MTK_PPE_BIND_LIMIT0_HALF;
